    "faq_atNR83": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_ztTR4d": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What accessories do I need for an electric bike?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>The best ebike accessories depend on how you ride. For commuting, start with a secure lock, a phone mount, and mirrors for visibility. For errands and travel, add a front/rear basket or pannier bag for cargo and daily storage.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_xN8RTP": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are Jasion accessories compatible with all Jasion ebike models?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Many accessories are designed to be broadly compatible across Jasion ebikes (like locks, mirrors, and phone mounts). Model-specific items—especially <strong>battery packs</strong>—must match your exact bike series. Always confirm compatibility on the product page before ordering.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_FrfnrY": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do you sell replacement batteries and extra battery packs?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Yes. We offer battery packs for specific models/series (for example, X-Hunter, Hunter Pro) so you can extend range or keep a spare for longer rides.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_xmky3P": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I choose between a front basket, rear basket, and pannier bag?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Choose based on what you carry and how often you ride with cargo. A <strong>front basket</strong> is great for quick access items, a <strong>rear basket</strong> is ideal for larger loads, and a <strong>rack pannier bag</strong> keeps items protected and stable—especially for commuting.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_hj4Dpj": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I carry a pet using Jasion accessories?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>We offer a dedicated <a href=\"https://www.jasionbike.com/products/copy-of-jasion%C2%AEbike-rack-pannier-bag\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>pet bike basket</strong></a> designed for riders who want to bring a small companion along. For the safest experience, follow the product instructions and ensure the basket is securely mounted before every ride.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_AjDfTx": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What’s the best lock for an ebike?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>For higher theft-risk areas, a U-lock style is typically a strong choice. For everyday stops, a combination lock can be convenient. No matter which you choose, lock the frame to a fixed object and park in a visible, well-lit area when possible.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_VQrVyz": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are mirrors and phone mounts worth it for commuting?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Yes—mirrors improve situational awareness, and a phone mount helps with navigation without stopping. For daily riders, these two upgrades are among the simplest ways to make commuting safer and more convenient.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_NV4Bek": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do accessories require professional installation?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Most common accessories (baskets, locks, mirrors, phone mounts, bags) are designed for straightforward installation. For model-specific parts or fit-critical accessories, follow the instructions on the product page and contact support if you have questions.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_YhYd8Q": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I improve passenger comfort with accessories?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Yes. If you ride with a passenger setup, comfort upgrades like a rear seat accessory can improve stability and support. Always follow the product guidance and confirm your bike’s payload limits before riding with passengers.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_zaYRat": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I know which accessory is right for my riding style?",
            "title_tag": "h3",
            "text": "<p>Start with your primary use case: <strong>commuting</strong> (lock + mirrors + phone mount), <strong>cargo/errands</strong> (basket or pannier), <strong>longer rides</strong> (spare battery pack), or <strong>family/pet trips</strong> (pet basket / seat accessories). If you’re unsure, pick one “safety” upgrade and one “cargo” upgrade first—those usually deliver the biggest day-to-day benefit.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
